				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\mathbf {J}$$\end{document} added in the DEPOSIT subroutine as a source term in Maxwell’s equations is divided into four contributions of which only two are kept in the cell, whilst the other two are deposited in the cells to each side. This is equivalent to “convolving” the flux array with the sequence 0.25, 0.5, and 0.25 and is performed individually in each of the three dimensions.

