An algorithm is presented that incorporates the Kerr–Schild metric of rotating black holes in PIC codes (Watson and Nishikawa 2010). The algorithm and implementation for the simulation of charged particles are described in the region of a spinning black hole. They have tested the overall model by using a ‘toy’ black hole and accretion disk system in a uniform magnetic field which has shown the production of bipolar jets.Fig. 35
