It is noteworthy that equatorward return currents appear inside the ergosphere in the lower-middle latitudes. They enable the magnetosphere to electromagnetically extract the BH’s rotational energy via the Blandford–Znajek (BZ) process (Blandford and Znajek 1977). Henceforth, the problem with the BZ process in relation to the causality and the plasma’s inertia (Punsly 1996), which assumed a stationary and axisymmetric magnetosphere, can be overcome by the formation of these strong (but finite) meridional return currents near (but outside) the event horizon, when a magnetically-dominated BH magnetosphere becomes highly time-dependent due to plasma oscillations (see Fig. 4 of Hirotani et al. 2021).Fig. 37
