Their arguments so far have been general and have not relied on any specific geometry. In order to demonstrate the validity of their arguments they have presented numerical results for a particular case. They considered the so-called giant attosecond pulse generation in the process of an over-dense plasma irradiation by an ultra-relativistic laser in the relativistic electronic spring regime (Gonoskov et al. 2011). They chose this example because it is a ‘worst case’ scenario; a very wide (far beyond I∼ω-8/3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
